article.headline: Wagner 45, Iona 28
article.story: NEW YORK -- Prince Young ran for 128 yards and two touchdowns and Wagner scored 38 consecutive points in a 45-28 victory over Iona Saturday. After the visiting Gaels (1-1) took a 7-0 lead on Craig Sutera's 3-yard run at 11:57 of the first quarter, Tyrone Collins returned the ensuing kickoff 86 yards to tie the game and start the 38-0 run. Wagner (1-1) took the lead Young's 11-yard run at 1:48 of the first quarter. The freshman had 19 carries. Seahawks quarterback Adam Farnsworth ran 1 yard for a score at 7:02 of the second quarter and connected on a 12-yard TD pass to Lon Woods at 2:20 for a 28-7 lead. Eric Ortiz kicked a 31-yard field goal as time expired in the first half. Shane Smith, who led Wagner with 174 yards on 19 carries, added a 41-yard TD run at 8:18 of the third period. Iona, led by quarterback Warren Smith, got back in the game by scoring three straight touchdowns. Smith ran in from 11 yards at 2:41 of the third, hit Nick Groth for a 14-yard TD pass with 47 seconds left in the period and ran in again from 12 yards out at 3:45 of the fourth quarter to make it 38-28. Young's finished the scoring with a 4-yard run with 58 seconds left.
